INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (3,1,'2005-04-30 12:56:58','2005-04-30 16:56:58','My old weblog has been broken for a long time.  There have been plenty of things I would have posted about but wasn\'t able to.  Pardon my long silence.  Chad wrote the old software and suggested I switch to something like Wordpress, which I\'m now using, because he\'s simply just been too busy to support the old kellyjeanne.org.  This way, I can get help from documentation if I need it and he doesn\'t feel bad when I say things like \"I\'d sure like to write a post on my website about that\".','New Blog',0,'','publish','open','open','','new-blog','','','2005-04-30 13:38:19','2005-04-30 17:38:19','',0,'http://kellyjeanne.org/?p=3',0),(4,1,'2005-04-30 13:22:19','2005-04-30 17:22:19','We pre-ordered Tiger and it was delivered and installed last night.  The only obvious visual difference (for me) is a spotlight icon on the menu bar and a dashboard icon on the dock.  Dashboard is fun and I can see it becoming a useful tool for things like tracking packages with FedEx and UPS, tracking flights (!yay!), etc.  I love the dictionary/thesaurus widget, and I downloaded a lovely hula girl and the \"creaturesinmyhead.com widgets last night.  I was amazed at how quickly new widgets started popping up last night.  In the space of just a few minutes (it seemed) the widget count on http://www.apple.com/downloads/macosx/dashboard went from 42 to 47....it\'s now up to 51 (so maybe that\'s not so impressive).  Spotlight is pretty neat, but I\'m a freak and know where all my documents, pictures etc..are already anyway.  I guess if I\'m looking for some kind of system file it\'ll be useful.  Mail..... the jury is still out.  RSS is pretty neat, but I can\'t say that I actually use it currently, maybe that\'ll change.  iChat AV... I\'ll let you know when I actually need to video conference with 3 other people how it works out.. heheh..  I do like the \"Current iTunes Track\" feature though.  I haven\'t played around with the Automator yet, I\'ll definitely let you know how that goes.  Other than that, the computer is running great, lets see what happens! ','Tiger',0,'','publish','open','open','','tiger','','','2005-04-30 13:22:19','2005-04-30 17:22:19','',0,'http://kellyjeanne.org/?p=4',0),(5,1,'2005-04-30 14:08:35','2005-04-30 18:08:35','We recently went on a trip with Walter and ME.  I\'d link to his website, but he currenty doesn\'t have one.  We met at Land Between the Lakes in Western Kentucky since it\'s halfway.  Thanks to those guys for asking us to go and then following through to make sure it happened.  We had a great time.  Highlights include allowing Walter to be in charge of making the margaritas and then setting the pace for drinking them, and the fateful boat ride.   I found this great photo of Captain Walter and First Mate Mary Ellen.  They look really happy.  It\'s only because the fear and ridiculousness of what we were doing made it impossible not to.  \r\n\r\n<center><img src=\"images/laughingwme.jpg\"/></center>\r\n\r\nLong story short: We rented a boat. We gassed it up. It started to rain.  We drove it out anyway. Cleared the marina. It started to rain harder.  Thunder. Lightening. Laughing. Return to Marina and face Marina employees who are laughing at the freaks who took the boat out in the storm. End of story.  ','Found a great photo!',0,'','publish','open','open','','found-a-great-photo','','','2005-04-30 14:08:42','2005-04-30 18:08:42','',0,'http://kellyjeanne.org/?p=5',0),(6,1,'2005-04-30 15:34:06','2005-04-30 19:34:06','The banner photo on the top of the page is of pottery created by yours truly.  Ceramics was one of my many college majors.  I stuck with it the longest.  I really loved it.  I was very happy during that time and reflected fondly upon it for years.  Last summer I decided to start taking classes again.  I think I can say that next to marrying Chad it was the best decision I\'ve made.  I love it.  I was really lucky and found a <b>great</b> teacher, Suzy.  We\'re about the same age and have similar interests and senses of humor.  The best part is: I\'m really learning from her.  Soon I\'ll have my own studio setup.  We\'re still debating whether it should be at the house or in a rented space.  Either way it will be the realization of a long standing dream.  ','About the Pottery',0,'','publish','open','open','','about-the-pottery','','','2005-04-30 15:34:20','2005-04-30 19:34:20','',0,'http://kellyjeanne.org/?p=6',0),(7,1,'2005-05-05 12:27:34','2005-05-05 16:27:34','I took the plunge last night after much coaxing from my teacher, my sister and Chad.  I ordered a wheel.  It\'s a Bailey Wheel.  I\'ve never used one, but it had a lot of great features, was a pretty great price and I think it\'ll work out well for me.  \r\n\r\n<center><img src=\"images/pottery/wheel.jpg\"/></center>\r\n\r\nIt\'s white and pretty, which won\'t last long.  Soon it\'ll be dirty and used.  It has some great features that I won\'t bore the non-artsy fartsy types with, but one of the best, worth mentioning features is the optional counter.  \r\n\r\n<center><img src=\"images/pottery/counter.jpg\"/></center>\r\n\r\nWhat\'s great about the counter is, you get more room for your tools and take up less space in your studio with an extra table or shelf, whatever.  \r\n\r\nI can\'t wait.  ','Step one in Dream Realization',0,'','publish','open','open','','step-one-in-dream-realization','','','2005-05-05 12:27:34','2005-05-05 16:27:34','',0,'http://kellyjeanne.org/?p=7',0),(8,1,'2005-05-06 10:51:13','2005-05-06 14:51:13','<a href=\"http://www.hisessence.com/\">His Essence Official Website -- Creations to Comfort the Soul</a>\r\n\r\n\r\nI don\'t really have to say anything do I?','His Essence Official Website -- Creations to Comfort the Soul',0,'','publish','open','open','','his-essence-official-website-creations-to-comfort-the-soul','','','2005-05-06 10:51:13','2005-05-06 14:51:13','',0,'http://kellyjeanne.org/?p=8',0),(9,1,'2005-05-07 13:38:40','2005-05-07 17:38:40','I turned 35 in December.... EEEK!  For my birthday, I got something I\'ve wanted for a long time.  An Aquarium!  I was really happy and looking forward to adding some fishy friends to our household.   I found a great looking tank that would fit well in the house and I could sit next to it and enjoy the sound of the running water and watching the fish swim swim swim.  Here\'s the tank:\r\n\r\n<center><img src=\"images/aquarium/talltank.jpg\"/></center>\r\n\r\nWe bought it the day before my birthday so that I could set it up and then add fish to it the next day.  It takes about 4 to 6 weeks for the tank to completely \"cycle\" and be hospitable for most fish.  You can cycle the tank with a hardy species like the Zebra Danios I chose to cycle with.  I\'ve since learned that this is quite stressful for the fish and you can cycle the tank without putting the fish through it.  Well, let me tell you.  I love the danios, they\'re fun fish and believe it or not (Chad thinks I\'m crazy) have a lot of personality.  Problem is, they\'re asskickers.  They\'ve pretty much killed every other fish I\'ve put in the tank with them since the cycle completed.  I\'ve joked for a long time that our house and yard are basically a small animal version of the Texas Chainsaw Massacre *see footnote* and the danios are only helping re-inforce that theory.  The Solution?  Return the danios to the store and see if I can get some Angelfish to survive in the tank.  I\'ll be doing that on Monday.  I hate to do it, but I don\'t want to kill any more fish and I can\'t get anything but danios to live in the tank as long as these 5 serial killer fish are in there.  Angelfish can grow to be about 6 inches tall and need a pretty big tank to feel comfortable, my tank will be a perfect fit for them.  I\'m looking forward to bringing them home.  \r\n\r\nAbout a month ago I bought another tank.  I know it seems crazy, but I did.  Apparently this is very common in fishkeeping, you get one tank, catch \"the bug\" and many many tanks are added to your collection.  Here\'s the new beauty:\r\n\r\n<center><img src=\"images/aquarium/bowtank.jpg\"/></center>\r\n\r\nI got it setup and cycled in about 3-1/2 weeks.  I used a biological additive to get the cycle going and \"fed\" the tank everyday to help speed up the proccess.  I\'ve currently got 3 cory cats and 5 gold tetras swimming in it now.  The large driftwood in the center has got some live plants(Java Moss) rubber banded to it, once they\'re established the rubber band will come off.  Here\'s a photo of the tetras:\r\n\r\n<center><img src=\"images/aquarium/tetras.jpg\"/></center>\r\n\r\nIt\'s hard to take pictures of fish.  It\'s hard to take pictures of aquariums, period.  You can\'t use a flash because it reflects off the glass, and for some reason, you can\'t get the fish to sit still.  Imagine.  The tetras are pretty interested in me.  I know, I know, sounds crazy, but if I sit close to the tank and watch them, they\'ll come over and watch me too.  They\'re a really nice schooling tetra and quite pretty.  They\'re very shiny and their scales shimmer and are very metallic gold.  They\'re small now but grow very quickly and will eventually be about 1-1/2 to 1-3/4 inches.  (two of these guys look a little silver to me and seem to have a faint black stripe that the others don\'t have, maybe I have two black neon tetras too? or some kind of hybrid?) Chad really wanted to see some big fish, so he was really disappointed when he came home to these tiny guys.  Hopefully the angels will make him happy when he sees those.  \r\n\r\n*footnote* - - We have 4 dogs.  One of them is a retired racing Greyhound.  He used to chase a furry thing around and around in a circle for a living.  He never got to catch it.  Until he came home to our house.  Suddenly he was able to catch the running furry thing.  I think that was the happiest day of his life.  He sure didn\'t understand why I wasn\'t as happy as he was.  Since then it had been a pretty steady stream of small animal deaths.  Eventually I think they were all killed or established some kind of early warning system to warn off the new neighborhood critters from the \"Yard of Death\".  Occasionally something gets in, usually they\'re able to escape through some strategically place holes, sometimes they fight back as in the case of the groundhog that wouldn\'t die, sometimes they don\'t make it.  We don\'t like it, we try to avoid it whenever possible, but the poor dog is only doing what centuries of breeding and 5 years of racing has taught him.  It\'s almost as though we have our very own National Geographic safari park in our backyard. Cycle of life and all that. After Greg the Greyhound came Arnie.  Arnie can catch birds.  He also really likes to dig up moles.  One day I looked out in tbe backyard and Arnie was happily tossing this brown lump in the air and catching it and tossing it again.  In my head I heard \"WHEE!!! WHEE!!!!\"  Upon further investigation the lump turned out to be a gigantic mole he\'d finally dug up.  The hole was so deep he could stand in it and we could barely see him.  YaY.  \r\n\r\nSo, on that note, somehow the addition of some murderous Zebra Danios isn\'t all that suprising.  ','Fishies!',0,'','publish','open','open','','fishies','','','2005-05-07 13:41:43','2005-05-07 17:41:43','',0,'http://kellyjeanne.org/?p=9',0),(10,1,'2005-05-09 21:11:50','2005-05-10 01:11:50','I brought home my new Angelfishes today.  I\'m really lucky to have such a great LFS (Live Fish Shop) so close to the house with not only great healthy fish, but helpful and responsible employees (for the most part).  \r\n\r\nI brought home 4 gorgeous new Angels for my 44 gallon pentagonal aquarium.  \r\n\r\nHere\'s a shot of one of my new, let\'s call her canary yellow, Angels:\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n<center><img src=\"images/aquarium/yellowangel.jpg\"/></center>\r\n<br />\r\nI\'m calling it a her because she\'s so dainty compared to the other three and a bit smaller in size.\r\n\r\n\r\nI also got a really great shot of the other three fellows that came home with her(?):\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n<center><img src=\"images/aquarium/3angels.jpg\"/></center>\r\n<br />\r\n\r\nTwo of these guys are called \"Clown\" Angels.  They\'re very iridescent and with good water quality and good food that should increase with age.  The yellow girl should become a brilliant gold, although I\'m hoping she\'ll retain some of her nice yellow color as well, and the biggest guy I haven\'t been able to put my finger on what his color variation is, but it\'s possible he\'s what they call a calico.  We\'ll see...give me a few more days to watch them and do some research on the internet and I\'ll have some answers for you. (not that any of you probably care much...hehe)\r\n\r\nWish me luck, I\'ll need it.  ','New Fish',0,'','publish','open','open','','new-fish','','','2005-05-10 11:00:20','2005-05-10 15:00:20','',0,'http://kellyjeanne.org/?p=10',0),(11,1,'2005-06-02 22:38:28','2005-06-03 02:38:28','I\'m all set up in my new studio with my wheel and clay and tools.  My father-in-law came over this morning and helped me schlep my stuff over to the studio.  This afternoon I went back and started moving everything around.  I managed to get everything put away pretty quickly and organized the way I think I\'ll like it... which led to actually getting some clay ready and breakin\' that sucker in.  Pretty GREAT!  That nice white shiny wheel you saw in the pictures is no more.. It\'s officially muddy. A dream came true today.  :)  Pictures soon! ','It\'s Official',0,'','publish','open','open','','its-official','','','2005-06-02 22:54:23','2005-06-03 02:54:23','',0,'http://kellyjeanne.org/?p=11',0),(12,1,'2005-06-05 16:59:10','2005-06-05 20:59:10','When I first started thinking about having an aquarium, I went to the pet store up the street and looked at all the fishes so I could make up my mind if it was really something I wanted to get in to.  I saw the most beautiful fish called a Ram there.  He was not very big, but he was so coloful and interesting that I was instantly enamored.  So, I started setting up and aquarium thinking maybe one day if I was really serious I could bring one or two home.<br />\r\n \r\n\r\nLast week, I brought a tiny pair home.  Turns out I got a male and female purely by chance.  They\'re still very young, but growing quickly, two days ago they laid some eggs..  they didn\'t take, but if this keeps up, I might be up to my eyeballs in baby fish soon... EEK!  Wish me luck. <br />\r\n\r\n<center />Here\'s a pic of my little mohawk wearing punk rockers. <br />(The male is in the foreground, the female upper left corner)\r\n\r\n<center /><img src=\"images/aquarium/smallrampic.jpg\"/>','Punk Rock Fishies',0,'','publish','open','open','','punk-rock-fishies','','','2005-10-15 11:33:12','2005-10-15 15:33:12','',0,'http://kellyjeanne.org/?p=12',0),(13,1,'2005-06-27 00:15:49','2005-06-27 04:15:49','We\'re home after a week in Seattle. At 11pm Louisville feels a bit, let\'s just say, balmy.  \r\n\r\nGood to be home, 4 dogs, still alive and perhaps a little fatter.  We missed the little buggers.','Home Again, Home Again',0,'','publish','open','open','','home-again-home-again','','','2005-06-27 00:15:49','2005-06-27 04:15:49','',0,'http://kellyjeanne.org/?p=13',0),(14,1,'2005-09-07 11:15:47','2005-09-07 15:15:47','This summer I was driving down the road here in Louisville, thinking about how busy I am here and all our friends and it suddenly hit me that we\'ve been here for 6 years! I panicked! Oh My God!  6 years in one city!  That\'s a really long time for me...  I\'m not sure I\'m ready for this kind of commitment!  We could very well stay here for the rest of our lives and probably be pretty happy.  WE NEED TO MOVE!  That was my thought proccess.  I didn\'t really seriously consider moving it was just one of those moments you have when you\'re mind is quiet and you examine your situation.  \r\n\r\nThe funny thing is, here we are 2 or 3 months later and we\'re moving!  Chad has taken a dream job and it happens to be in a dream place.  We\'re moving to Denver, Colorado this fall.  We\'re both really excited and looking forward to a new house and new city.  We\'re also sad to leave a great city and great friends.  Luckily with the internet, the telephone and transportation, we can keep in touch and maintain lasting bonds with people even though we\'re not in the same city any more.  Don\'t look at it like you\'re losing your friends, look at it like you\'re getting a new place to go on vacation. ','Colorado or Bust!',0,'','publish','open','open','','colorado-or-bust','','','2005-09-07 11:15:47','2005-09-07 15:15:47','',0,'http://kellyjeanne.org/?p=14',0),(15,1,'2005-10-31 00:10:34','2005-10-31 04:10:34','','Still Crazy... After all these years. ',0,'','draft','open','open','','still-crazy-after-all-these-years','','','2005-10-31 00:10:34','2005-10-31 04:10:34','',0,'http://kellyjeanne.org/?p=15',0),(16,1,'2005-10-31 00:10:34','2005-10-31 04:10:34','','Still Crazy... After all these years. ',0,'','draft','open','open','','still-crazy-after-all-these-years','','','2005-10-31 00:10:34','2005-10-31 04:10:34','',0,'http://kellyjeanne.org/?p=16',0),(17,1,'2005-10-31 00:22:39','2005-10-31 04:22:39','Some of you may remember a lovely picture of poor Greg the Greyhound who refused to acknowledge the fact that he\'s gigantic and not a tiny little tidbit of a dog like Polkadot. \r\n\r\nHere\'s a photo that graced my website for a long time. <br />\r\n<center>\r\n<img src=\"images/dogs/bigdoglittlebed2.jpg\"/></center>\r\n<br />\r\nHe wanted to fit in that bed so badly it was almost painful to watch.  Many times the bed was the focus of his frustration when things didn\'t go his way or he couldn\'t fit his massive body into it.  Sadly it perished some time ago.  \r\n<br />\r\nI recently brought home a nice shiny new even smaller bed for the chihuahuas.. they insist on sharing at all times.  Very rarely will you see one laying in it alone. \r\n<br />\r\n<center><img src=\"images/dogs/littleones.jpg\"/></center>\r\n<br />\r\nApparently, Greg hasn\'t given up hope that he too will fit into the new little bed.   I think someone is trying to tell us he would like his own little slice of bed shaped foam heaven.  What do you think?\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n<center><img src=\"images/dogs/bigheadlittlebed.jpg\"/></center>','Still Crazy... After all these years. ',0,'','publish','open','open','','still-crazy-after-all-these-years','','','2005-10-31 00:24:27','2005-10-31 04:24:27','',0,'http://kellyjeanne.org/?p=17',0),(18,1,'2005-11-20 00:49:25','2005-11-20 04:49:25','','We live in Colorado.',0,'','publish','open','open','','we-live-in-colorado','','','2005-11-20 00:49:25','2005-11-20 04:49:25','',0,'http://kellyjeanne.org/?p=18',0),(19,1,'2005-11-30 21:06:54','2005-12-01 01:06:54','<center><img src=\"http://www.kellyjeanne.org/dropbox/SecondWeekColorado/KellyAndArnieWalkingIntoSun.JPG\"/>\r\n<p>\r\nArnie and Me walking in our neighborhood\'s Open Space. </p></center>','Walking',0,'','publish','open','open','','walking','','','2005-11-30 21:08:06','2005-12-01 01:08:06','',0,'http://kellyjeanne.org/?p=19',0);
